---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'Header';
---

<BaseLayout title={title}>
  <div class="docs-page">
    <nav><a href="/docs/test_pages/">&larr; Test Pages</a></nav>
    <div class="prose">
      <h1>Header</h1>

      <p>Site-wide header rendered at the top of every page by <code>BaseLayout</code>. Ported from the Hugo <code>main-nav</code> partial — dimensions, colors, shadows, breakpoints, hover timings, and interactions all match the Hugo site. The header you see above this content is the component itself.</p>

      <h2>Sub-components</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Component</th><th>Type</th><th>Role</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>Header.astro</code></td><td>Astro (static)</td><td>Nav shell — reads menu data at build time and renders logo, left menu, right menu, and hamburger statically for SEO.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>NavDropdown.tsx</code></td><td>Preact island</td><td>Hover-open dropdown used for Solutions, About, and Blog menus. Opens on mouse-enter, closes 150ms after mouse-leave.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>ProductMegaMenu.tsx</code></td><td>Preact island</td><td>The Product dropdown. Holds <code>openCategory</code> state with a 160ms hover debounce; resets to the first category when the dropdown closes.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>LogoDownloadPanel.astro</code></td><td>Static + tiny <code>&lt;script is:inline&gt;</code></td><td>Hidden "Looking for Datadog logos?" popover. Click-toggle behavior mirrors Hugo's <code>.js-logo-download</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>HeaderScroll.astro</code></td><td><code>&lt;script is:inline&gt;</code></td><td>Adds <code>.main-nav-scrolled</code> to <code>&lt;html&gt;</code> once <code>scrollY &gt; 30</code> at ≥992px (matching Hugo's <code>tailwind-main-nav.html</code>). The class snaps the nav from 130→65px, animates the bits logo 75→50px, and hides the wordmark — all via a shared 200ms ease-in-out transition.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>MobileNav.tsx</code></td><td>Preact island</td><td>Hamburger-triggered right-side overlay. Renders the docs mobile nav variant with home/docs/api quick-links, search stub, and full menu tree. Receives already-resolved labels and URLs as props so the client bundle doesn't pull in <code>menuData</code> / <code>i18n</code> / <code>yaml</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>NavIcon.astro</code></td><td>Static</td><td>Renders a websites-modules iconfont icon (<code>&lt;i class="icon-&#123;name&#125;"&gt;</code>) and colors it with <code>currentColor</code>.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Data flow</h2>
      <p>Menu data is assembled at build time by <code>getHeaderData()</code> in <code>src/lib/componentUtils/menuData.ts</code>, which reads <code>data/menu_data/*.yaml</code> directly from <code>@websites-modules</code>, runs labels through <code>i18n(key)</code>, and resolves URLs so relative paths become <code>https://www.datadoghq.com/…</code>. The component receives a single structured view model with named slots (<code>product</code>, <code>solutions</code>, <code>about</code>, <code>blog</code>, <code>login</code>, <code>getStarted</code>, <code>simpleLeft</code>, <code>mobileItems</code>, <code>mobileCategories</code>) — no <code>find</code>/<code>filter</code> in the template.</p>

      <h2>Dimensions (Hugo-identical)</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Viewport</th><th>Header height</th><th>Behavior on scroll</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>&lt;992px</td><td>60px</td><td>No change</td></tr>
          <tr><td>≥992px, <code>scrollY ≤ 30</code></td><td>130px</td><td>Resting state.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>≥992px, <code>scrollY &gt; 30</code></td><td>65px</td><td><code>.main-nav-scrolled</code> is added: the nav, bits logo, and wordmark all transition together over 200ms ease-in-out.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <p>The corresponding tokens live in the Hugo-identical section of <code>src/styles/tokens.css</code>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .docs-page {
    max-width: 960px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
  }

  h1 {
    border-bottom: var(--border-width-thick) solid var(--color-border-strong);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }
</style>
